## ApiSources-P3 Model-First Agent Configuration
**Status:** draft
**Tags:** stack:both, module:api-sources
**Depends on:** ApiSources-G3, ApiSources-A3, ApiSources-D1

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P3.1 | Add `model_id: String` to `AgentConfig` struct | Coder | 1h | — | draft | Add `#[serde(default)] pub model_id: String` field to `AgentConfig` in `backend/src/relay/config.rs` (~line 379). Keep `model_tier` with `#[serde(default)]` for backward compat. Both fields serialize/deserialize without error on old/new JSON. Per D1 §1 AgentConfig. **File:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs` **Deliverable:** struct compiles, existing JSON configs with only `model_tier` still deserialize (model_id defaults to ""). |
| P3.2 | Simplify `resolve_model()` to direct model_id lookup | Coder | 1h | P3.1 | draft | Replace tier downgrade walk (~lines 548-586) with: (1) find ApiSource by `config.api_source_id`, fallback first source; (2) find ModelDefinition by `config.model_id`, fallback first model + `log::warn!`. Return `ModelConfig { provider, model, temperature, max_tokens, reasoning_budget, fallback_chain }`. Per D1 §1 resolve_model(). **File:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs` **Deliverable:** no tier walk remains; unit test: resolve by model_id returns correct model; resolve with invalid model_id falls back to first model. |
| P3.3 | Add `assign_model_ids()` migration helper | Coder | 1h | P3.1 | draft | New `pub fn assign_model_ids(configs: &mut [AgentConfig], api_sources: &[ApiSource])` — for each config where `model_id.is_empty()`, find source, find first model matching `config.model_tier`, fallback first model. Log each migration via `log::info!`. Per D1 §1 assign_model_ids(). **File:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs` **Deliverable:** legacy config with tier but no model_id gets model_id populated after calling this function. |
| P3.4 | Update `generate_default_agents_with_source()` | Coder | 0.5h | P3.1 | draft | Set `model_id: String::new()` in generated defaults (migration fills it). Keep preferred_tier in `model_tier` field for assign_model_ids to use. Per D1 §1 generate_default_agents_with_source(). **File:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs` **Deliverable:** generated configs have empty model_id; other fields unchanged. |
| P3.5 | Wire `assign_model_ids()` into `load_or_generate_agent_configs()` | Coder | 0.5h | P3.3, P3.4 | draft | After merge of existing + defaults, call `assign_model_ids(&mut merged, api_sources)` before `save_agent_configs()`. Per D1 §1 load_or_generate_agent_configs(). **File:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs` **Deliverable:** any config loaded from disk without model_id gets it auto-filled on next startup. |
| P3.6 | Audit `mod.rs` for direct model_tier references | Coder | 0.5h | P3.2 | draft | Confirm `backend/src/relay/mod.rs` calls `resolve_model()` and doesn't reference `model_tier` directly. If any direct tier references exist in spawn logic, update to use resolved ModelConfig. Per A3 §Verified Code Locations. **File:** `backend/src/relay/mod.rs` **Deliverable:** `cargo check` passes; no model_tier reads outside config.rs migration code. |
| P3.7 | Update `AgentConfigDto` in frontend | Coder | 0.5h | — | draft | Add `model_id: string` to `AgentConfigDto` interface in `frontend/src/composables/useAgentConfigs.ts`. Keep `model_tier` for display badge. Per D1 §2 Frontend Changes. **File:** `frontend/src/composables/useAgentConfigs.ts` **Deliverable:** TypeScript compiles; existing API responses with model_id deserialize correctly. |
| P3.8 | Add `getModelsForSource()` helper to `useApiSources.ts` | Coder | 0.5h | — | draft | Add exported function `getModelsForSource(sourceId: string): ModelDefinition[]` that finds the ApiSource by ID and returns its models array. Expose from composable return. Per D1 §2 useApiSources. **File:** `frontend/src/composables/useApiSources.ts` **Deliverable:** function returns correct model list for a given source ID, empty array if not found. |
| P3.9 | Replace tier dropdown with model selector in `AgentsConfigView.vue` | Coder | 3h | P3.7, P3.8 | draft | (1) Compute `availableModels` from selected ApiSource using `getModelsForSource()`. (2) When `api_source_id` changes, auto-select first model and set `agent.model_id`. (3) Replace tier dropdown select with model selector showing `model.name + tierBadge(model.tier)`. (4) On model change, update `agent.model_id` and `agent.model_tier` from selected model. (5) Add tier badge CSS classes: Min=gray(#9ca3af), Lite=green(#22c55e), Mid=blue(#3b82f6), Pro=purple(#a855f7), Max=amber(#f59e0b). Per D1 §2 AgentsConfigView.vue. **File:** `frontend/src/views/AgentsConfigView.vue` **Deliverable:** model selector lists all models from selected source; tier badge shown next to each model; changing source auto-selects first model. |
| P3.10 | Add i18n keys for model selector | Coder | 0.5h | P3.9 | draft | Add `agents.model` key to `frontend/src/locales/en.json` ("Model") and `frontend/src/locales/zh.json` ("模型"). Rename or add alongside existing `agents.modelTier`. Per architect handoff Q-1. **Files:** `frontend/src/locales/en.json`, `frontend/src/locales/zh.json` **Deliverable:** model selector label uses `t('agents.model')`. |
| P3.11 | Backend compilation and unit tests | Coder | 1h | P3.1-P3.6 | draft | Run `cargo check -p auto-forge` and `cargo test -p auto-forge`. Write/update unit tests: (1) test resolve_model with valid model_id returns correct model; (2) test resolve_model with invalid model_id falls back to first; (3) test assign_model_ids migrates tier to model_id; (4) test serde round-trip with old JSON (no model_id) and new JSON (with model_id). **Deliverable:** all tests pass. |
| P3.12 | Frontend build and smoke test | Coder | 1h | P3.7-P3.10 | draft | Run `pnpm build`. Verify: (1) agent config cards show model selector instead of tier dropdown; (2) changing API source refreshes model list and auto-selects first; (3) tier badges render with correct colors; (4) saving config persists model_id to backend. **Deliverable:** build succeeds; manual verification confirms UX matches D1 wireframe. |

### Risks and Mitigations

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|--------|------------|
| Legacy JSON configs break on deserialization | Low | High | Both `model_id` and `model_tier` use `#[serde(default)]`; old JSON deserializes with model_id="" and migration fills it |
| ApiSource has no models matching preferred tier | Medium | Low | `assign_model_ids()` falls back to first model in source; `resolve_model()` falls back to first model with warning log |
| Frontend model selector shows stale list after source change | Low | Medium | Computed `availableModels` reactively depends on `agent.api_source_id`; watch triggers auto-select of first model |
| `resolve_model()` called before migration runs | Low | High | `load_or_generate_agent_configs()` calls `assign_model_ids()` before returning; all consumers get configs with model_id filled |
| `mod.rs` has hidden model_tier references | Medium | Medium | P3.6 explicitly audits `mod.rs` for any direct tier usage and updates to use resolved ModelConfig |

